* Minecraft

  * One of the most famous Java games ever made.
  * Originally developed entirely in Java.
  * Uses the LWJGL library for graphics and input.

* RuneScape

  * Browser-based for many years using Java applets.
  * One of the world's longest-running MMORPGs.

* Slay the Spire

  * A critically acclaimed roguelike deck-building game.
  * Built using the Java-based libGDX framework.

* Wurm Online

  * A sandbox MMORPG developed in Java.

## Android games

Since Android apps traditionally use Java, many early Android games were written in Java, such as:

* Temple Run (early Android versions)
* Subway Surfers (parts of the Android application)
* Angry Birds (Android application layer included Java)

> Note: Modern Android games often use Kotlin for the app layer and C++ (via the Android NDK) or engines like Unity or Unreal for the game itself.

## Indie games using Java frameworks

Many indie developers build games using Java frameworks like:

* libGDX
* jMonkeyEngine
* LWJGL
* FXGL

Common game types include:

* Platformers
* RPGs
* Tower defense games
* Puzzle games
* Multiplayer games
* Card games
* 2D shooters
* 3D sandbox games

